#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/guided-laplacian-highlights/index.md:2033
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A reconstruction that is measurably better but unusably slow would not ship. This section closes\n"
"the story with numbers : how the new method scales, what porting it to the graphics processor\n"
"(GPU, via OpenCL) bought, and how the old and new methods compare on the same machine and the\n"
"same images. The protocol behind every number below is the same : each timing is a full export\n"
"through `ansel-cli`, taken as the wall-clock\n"
"minimum of three runs on an otherwise idle machine, with module-internal timings read from the\n"
"built-in performance trace.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/resources/guided-laplacian-highlights/index.md:2034
#, no-wrap
msgid "Linear in the padded area"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/guided-laplacian-highlights/index.md:2054
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Asking \"how fast is the reconstruction per megapixel of image\" is the wrong question : an image\n"
"with no clipping costs almost nothing, and the same blown sun costs the same whether the frame\n"
"around it is 12 or 60 megapixels. The right variable falls out of the cost structure. Every heavy\n"
"stage of the shipped pipeline is linear in the **padded region area** — the clipped zone's extent\n"
"plus twice its reconstruction radius, squared — with constants independent of the fitting scale :\n"
"the windowed moments use recursive Gaussian filters whose cost does not depend on the window\n"
"size, the coefficient diffusion runs a fixed hundred-sweep budget per pyramid level on a base grid\n"
"that *shrinks* as the fitting scale grows (with the pyramid deep enough that its coarsest grid\n"
"is trivially small), and the luminance dome's direct solve is capped at a\n"
"constant number of unknowns (8,192, on a decimated grid) regardless of the hole. And since the\n"
"reconstruction radius *is* the\n"
"hole's deepest point, the padding is not a free parameter : a circular hole of radius $r$ needs a\n"
"padded region of roughly $(4r)^2$ — sixteen times the hole's own bounding box (the implementation\n"
"pads by $1.25\\\\,r$ — the minimum reach plus a $25\\\\,\\\\%$ safety margin — clamped between $8$ px,\n"
"so tiny specks still see context, and a $256$ px cost cap, so the very deepest holes grow\n"
"slightly slower than this law). Doubling a\n"
"highlight's diameter quadruples its cost, not because the algorithm is superlinear, but because\n"
"the reconstruction honestly needs to see that much more context.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/guided-laplacian-highlights/index.md:2062
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The bench (`make_perf_bench.py`, reproducible) consists of synthetic raws with one circular\n"
"clipped hole of\n"
"growing radius, in two families that exercise the two main code paths — a single clipped channel\n"
"(the coefficient field does the work) and all three channels clipped (the joint core does) —\n"
"timed through the production command-line pipeline, with every region of the three real test\n"
"images overlaid as measured points. The machine is an Intel Xeon E3-1505M v6, 4 cores / 8 threads at\n"
"3.0 GHz.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/guided-laplacian-highlights/index.md:2064
#, no-wrap
msgid "{{< plotly title=\"Runtime against padded region area (log-log). Both synthetic families follow the slope-1 reference over more than a decade; the real images’ regions — from a 0.1 Mpx sliver to PK1’s 15.8 Mpx sky — scatter in the same band.\" src=\"cf-perf-time.json\" caption=\"true\" >}}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/guided-laplacian-highlights/index.md:2066
#, no-wrap
msgid "{{< plotly title=\"The padding amplification : the region the algorithm must process grows as (4r)² for a hole of radius r, because the reconstruction radius equals the hole’s depth.\" src=\"cf-perf-padding.json\" caption=\"true\" >}}\n"
msgstr ""

